parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ABS sensor light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slows down unexpectedly
the vehicle lurches or surges forward when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the READY light lasts for less than 5 seconds and disappears
the vehicle cannot be started again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause electrical issues, leading to malfunctioning of various systems, including the brakes, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Water gets into the body of the vehicle
causing the passenger carpet to be soaked
the car smells like mildew
and the lights on the dash come on without rain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to become hard to push or activate, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels abnormally soft
the brakes become hard to push or activate
and the "CHECK VSC" system warning light comes on with a continuous beep noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lift gate handle can cause the handle to become sticky and gooey, making it difficult to open the rear door, and potentially causing electrical issues.
symptoms: The rear lift gate handle is melted and gooey
leaving a sticky substance on fingers
and the handle becomes inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alarm system can cause the alarm to go off randomly, potentially causing a disturbance and leading to safety concerns.
symptoms: The alarm goes off randomly
and the dealer is unable to diagnose the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting and cracking of the dashboard can cause reduced visibility, glare on the windshield, and potentially lead to airbag deployment issues, which can compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: Sticky or gummy dashboard
cracks on the dashboard
glare on the windshield
reduced visibility
airbag deployment concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting or peeling of the rear hatch and bumper components can cause difficulties in opening the hatch, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Melting or peeling of the rear hatch cover
difficulty opening the hatch
sticky or gooey rubber handle
peeling paint on the rear bumper.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spare tire cable, brake issues, and liftgate malfunction can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Spare tire cable failure
brake pedal "push" or failure to apply
liftgate malfunction
difficulty opening the hatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. The sudden surge of power can cause the vehicle to accelerate without warning, making it difficult for the driver to maintain control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the vehicle surges forward when braking
the vehicle hesitates or lurches forward when driving
the vehicle accelerates when the gas pedal is not depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hybrid system failure can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down
the hybrid system warning light comes on
the vehicle will not start
the vehicle displays a "check hybrid system" warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal surge can cause the vehicle to lurch forward, making it difficult to maintain control and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward when braking
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle hesitates or lurches forward when driving.
